FG-251 — Petition-for-Review Posture Card (Statute • Venue • Clock)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Agency review is statute-driven—map who/where/when on one card.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Card fields: Statute (review provision), Venue (D.C./regional), Clock (FR-publication/entry date → due), Record owner (agency). Add a one-line relief (vacate/remand or §705 stay).
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 6-line posture card for your agency action.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Statute: [Act §__]. Venue: D.C. Cir. Clock: 60 days from FR pub 08/01 → due 09/30. Relief: §705 stay or vacate/remand for reasoned decision.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Posture clarity wins calendar.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A small card showing Statute/Venue/Clock boxes.

⸻

FG-252 — §705 Stay (Agency/Fed) — Same Ask, Two Forums
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Seek §705 stay at agency or court with identical relief text.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Elements: likelihood + irreparable harm + equities + public interest; pin to rule text; offer narrow scope and status. File agency request + court motion in parallel; attach both.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a two-forum §705 stay (same language).
	•	✅ Model Response: “Relief: stay ¶3 pending review; pins: Agency Rule __; harm: vendor deadline (Decl ¶7). Status 14d; sunset 30d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Two lanes, one ask.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two courthouse icons feeding one stay card.

⸻

FG-253 — Federal Register Pin (Capture • Page • Hash)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: FR citations need capture date, page pin, and hash if hosted.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Cite volume/page; add “captured [date]”; if you host a PDF, list SHA-256; include a source URL in a footnote (not in text).
	•	📝 Assignment: Add a capture/hash line to one FR cite.
	•	✅ Model Response: “88 Fed. Reg. 12345 (Aug. 1, 2025) (captured 08/19; SHA-256 …).”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Official + captured = credible.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: An FR page tile with a tiny fingerprint footer.

⸻

FG-254 — Exhaustion Map (Issue • Step • Proof)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Show where each issue was raised below—or why it was futile.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Issue • Where raised (page/pin) • Agency ruling (or silence) • Proof; include futility row if allowed (bad faith, fixed policy).
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 6-row exhaustion table for your petition.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Notice timing — Comment p.12 — Agency ‘not reached’ — AR 118:12.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Exhaustion proved beats exhaustion argued.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A ladder of issue rows with check marks down “Raised.”

⸻

FG-255 — AR Completion vs. Supplement (Two Doors Only)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Complete the record (missing items) or supplement for background/technical context; never for new merits.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Motion headings: Identify omission (ID/page) or background need (methodology); cite exceptions (explain/technical); propose limited remand if truly extra-record.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft a 7-line AR completion/supplement motion with a fallback limited remand.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Relief: complete AR with Method Memo (AR Index #___) or consider technical background (Aff ¶¶3–5); alternatively limited remand 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Record first; context second; no new merits.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two small doors: “Complete” and “Supplement.”

⸻

FG-256 — Reasoned Decision Gap (State the Missing Step)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Identify the step missing under arbitrary-and-capricious review.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Use State the Gap formula: rule line → what agency failed to consider → pin to comment/AR → narrow remand text for reasoned response.
	•	📝 Assignment: Write a 6-line “reasoned decision gap” paragraph.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Agency never addressed timing harms raised at AR 118:12; under [cite], failure to consider important aspect requires remand to respond within 30 days.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Show the step, win the fix.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: A checklist with one box blank, circled in red.

⸻

FG-257 — Comment-to-Order Crosswalk (We Asked • They Skipped)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Map comment points to decision responses—the silence is your remedy.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Table: Comment topic • AR pin • Decision page • Response?; highlight “no response” rows; propose task-only remand for responses.
	•	📝 Assignment: Build a 10-row comment → response table.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Vendor timing — AR 118:12 — Decision p.7 — No response → remand to respond in 21d.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Crosswalks turn silence into orders.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Two columns linked by lines; missing lines in red.

⸻

FG-258 — Preserving Parallel Remedies (APA • Statutory • Constitutional)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Plead and preserve APA + statute + constitutional lanes without duplication.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Separate counts; state distinct elements; avoid cross-referencing facts as conclusions; end with aligned relief (vacate/remand).
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft three count headers with distinct elements and one aligned remedy paragraph.
	•	✅ Model Response: “Count II (APA): failure to consider timing; Count III (statutory): violates §__; Count IV (First Amendment): retaliation; Remedy: vacatur/remand for reasoned decision.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: Many lanes, one destination.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Three parallel tracks merging into “Vacate/Remand.”

⸻

FG-259 — Agency Record Legend (AR Doc • Dkt • Tab)
	•	⚖️ Core Message: Translate AR Doc IDs to your court’s Dkt/Tab once.
	•	📖 Lesson Content: Legend lines: “AR Doc __ at p.__ ↔ Dkt __ at __ ↔ Appx Tab __ p.__”; place on front matter; reuse in addendum.
	•	📝 Assignment: Draft five legend lines for your anchor documents.
	•	✅ Model Response: “AR 118:12 ↔ Dkt 18 at 2 ↔ Tab 3 p.2.”
	•	💡 Reflection Summary: One translator saves hours.
	•	🎨 Visual Concept: Three tags (AR/Dkt/Tab) linked by arrows.

⸻

